# ============================================================================
# The framework / private boundary.
#
# This repo is a PUBLIC genealogy-research FRAMEWORK. It is developed alongside
# a PRIVATE vault of real family data that must never be committed. Everything
# below encodes where that line falls.
#
# WHY THIS FILE AND NOT .git/info/exclude: an exclude file is machine-local and
# is NEVER part of a clone. Rules that live only there protect the original
# author's working tree and nobody else's — a forker inherits none of them. The
# boundary is a property of the PROJECT, so it belongs in a tracked file.
#
# Two different defaults below, on purpose (see CONTRIBUTING.md):
#   scripts/   -> TRACK by default (it is framework code)
#   doc dirs   -> IGNORE by default (they hold research prose full of real names)
# ============================================================================


# --- 1. Editor / OS / environment junk --------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.obsidian/
.github-triage/
privacy-audits/

# Python environment (managed by uv; reproduced from uv.lock, never committed).
# Especially important here: this repo lives in OneDrive — a synced .venv would
# upload thousands of interpreter files with machine-specific absolute paths.
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc


# --- 2. The private vault, and anything naming a real person ----------------
# A vault holds living people, birth dates and record identifiers. Never track
# one. `vault/` is the conventional single-vault path; `vault-<name>/` is the
# multi-vault layout (one toolkit, many client vaults).
vault/
vault-*/
# ...except the EMPTY starter kit, which is framework and IS tracked.
!vault-template/

# Per-client Claude instructions: the subject, the lineage->file layout, the
# generation anchors. Real family names by construction.
CLAUDE.instance.md
CLAUDE.local.md

# Operator-local config and the anonymization denylist (a list of the exact
# private terms — the most sensitive file in the tree).
.private/
.claude/


# --- 3. Personal design lanes ------------------------------------------------
# spec/ is a framework directory and its top-level docs ARE tracked, as are the
# four lanes that shipped with the public framework. The lanes below are
# personal planning scaffolding, not published design docs.
#
# Ignore the FILES inside spec subdirs (not the dirs themselves) so a lane can
# be opted in later with a !negation. Already-tracked files are unaffected —
# .gitignore never un-tracks anything.
spec/*/*.md
!spec/github-triage-lane/*.md
!spec/image-archive-deep-dive/*.md
!spec/normie-usability/*.md
!spec/safety-ux-polish/*.md


# --- 4. scripts/ : TRACK BY DEFAULT (inverted 2026-07-23) -------------------
# This directory used to read "ignore scripts/*.py, then re-add ~19 files by
# name". That default-to-private shape is exactly how `vault_config.py` stayed
# untracked while 15 of the scripts that IMPORT it were tracked: a fresh clone
# hit ImportError across nearly the whole toolkit, including every test.
#
# Framework code now defaults to TRACKED. Only genuinely local things are listed
# here. A new script is tracked unless you add it below — and the pre-commit
# privacy audit is what stops a script containing real names from going public.
# (gitignore has no inline comments — each note goes on its own line.)
# one-shot migrations for the retired Person_Index:
scripts/archive/
# operator's local scratch notes:
scripts/README.md
# accumulated FamilySearch walk data (real PIDs):
scripts/.buildout_data.json
# one-shot; reads a hand-built /tmp map:
scripts/apply_gen_fix.py
# meta-tool for triaging this very boundary:
scripts/contrib_triage.py


# --- 5. Research prose: IGNORE BY DEFAULT -----------------------------------
# prompts/ reference/ workflows/ are a MIX. Upstream's generic methodology is
# tracked; the operator's research notes are saturated with real surnames and
# places (one local reference file matched 44 private terms).
#
# The default here is the OPPOSITE of scripts/ because the failure modes are not
# symmetric: an ignored script breaks a clone, while an accidentally tracked
# research note discloses living people. To publish a new generic doc, opt it in
# with a !negation, as the tracked ones below are.
prompts/*.md
reference/*.md
workflows/*.md

!prompts/README.md
!prompts/[0-9][0-9]-*.md
# ...but these numbered prompts are this vault's own research lane, not
# framework prompts (and the repo contract pairs each numbered prompt with a
# human-review card, which these have no public counterpart for).
prompts/13-mayflower-lines-cascade.md
prompts/14-split-abington-file.md
prompts/15-tree-expansion-british-italian.md
prompts/16-aad-military-sweep.md
prompts/17-familysearch-tree-contribution.md
prompts/18-edge-verification.md
prompts/19-fs-source-harvest.md
prompts/20-creative-vault-review.md
prompts/_archive/

# Generic framework methodology (no vault content, placeholder names only).
!reference/common-pitfalls.md
!reference/confidence-tiers.md
!reference/dna-interpretation-guardrails.md
!reference/gedcom-guide.md
!reference/github-triage-lane.md
!reference/glossary.md
!reference/naming-conventions.md
!reference/source-hierarchy.md
!reference/vault-file-manifest.md
!reference/what-ai-can-and-cannot-do.md
!reference/why-autoresearch-for-genealogy.md

!workflows/discrepancy-resolution.md
!workflows/document-triage.md
!workflows/getting-started.md
!workflows/header-grammar.md
!workflows/image-archive-navigation.md
!workflows/new-ancestor-intake.md
!workflows/ocr-pipeline.md
!workflows/oral-history-protocol.md
!workflows/phase-planning.md
!workflows/shard-split.md
!workflows/structured-dates.md
!workflows/switch-person-model.md


